<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,310,1955]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1678,1703]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62">Distribution.</emphasis>
PALEARCTIC. Common and widespread in the boreal to low arctic parts of Europe; less common in the lowlands of western and central Europe south to the Alps. Outside Europe recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1372,1436,1715,1738]" name="Japan" pageId="11" pageNumber="62">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Suwa" box="[159,290,1751,1775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62" refString="Suwa, M. (1974) Anthomyiidae of Japan (Diptera). Insecta matsumurana (n. s.), 4, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1974">
Suwa 
<number box="[231,290,1751,1775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62" value="1974.1999">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Suwa" box="[303,362,1751,1775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62" refString="Suwa, M. (1999) Japanese records of anthomyiid flies (Diptera: Anthomyiidae). Insecta matsumurana (n. s.), 55, 203 - 244." type="journal article" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Suwa" box="[375,433,1750,1775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62" refString="Suwa, M. (2005) Supplemenrary notes on the family Anthomyiidae of Japan (Diptera), VI. Insecta matsumurana (n. s.), 61, 87 - 106." type="journal article" year="2005">
<number box="[375,433,1750,1775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[498,577,1750,1775]" name="Russia" pageId="11" pageNumber="62">Russia</collectingCountry>
: Altai, Sakha (new records). NEARCTIC. Common and widespread across boreal to low arctic North 
<collectingCountry box="[447,543,1786,1811]" name="United States of America" pageId="11" pageNumber="62">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Griffiths" box="[558,720,1786,1811]" pageId="11" pageNumber="62" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 161 - 288." type="journal article" year="1983">
